<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78863a98-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s719b–1"><num value="719b–1">§ 719b–1.</num><heading> Definition of State</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of this subchapter, the term “State” includes the District of Columbia, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, American Samoa, Guam, the Virgin Islands, and any other territory or possession of the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78863a99-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/340/s5">Pub. L. 103–340, § 5</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/106/316/s2/3">Pub. L. 106–316, § 2(3)</ref>, <date date="2000-10-19">Oct. 19, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1276">114 Stat. 1276</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7888aa9a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7888aa9b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id7888aa9c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior <ref href="/us/pl/103/340/s5">section 5 of Pub. L. 103–340</ref> was renumbered section 6 and is classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s719c">section 719c of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
